Well it has been quite some time since I have updated. hmm...

I have:
1. Marched Drum Corps
2. Pledged Phi Mu Alpha
3. been happily together with Ashlie for 7 months...

My life has been quite crazy the past few months but things have finally started to die down. I miss alot of my friends from home I am going to try to visit home now that I have time to do so. It seems so weird when I come back to Trussville now. It just seems different. I have been away for so long. It is not like I hate college its just that I want to visit the few friends I have left from highschool. 

I love Ashlie so much. She has always been there for me. I am so lucky to have someone like her in my life.

Yeah this semester has been real rough. I have been so busy. From drum corps to pledging I have been busy for almost 6 months straight. I am so glad that I am actually going to have some free time now. I need to study more often. My grades have really suffered this semester. I have a 3.1 this semester but by the end of this semester I am hoping for a 2.5 . I have to maintain that average to keep my scholarship. But oh well I should  be fine.


HS,
Stan

Well, drum corps has been kicking my ass for almost three weeks straight. It has been fun since I have been here but I never thought I was going to get my ass kicked this hard. We go on tour in 5 days and our first show is in 6 days in one of the Carolinas. I cannot wait to leave to go on tour, Im sick of this hell or all days that they are putting us through right now. Im sure it will all pay off at the end of the season because Im sure we will be in finals this year. DCI finals will be shown on ESPN 2 this year so look for us on TV in second week of August. Well rehearsal starts in about 30 min. so im going to rest for a little while.

Also, this past week has been great. I have got the girl ive been in love with ever since i have been in college. Ashlie Ross is the greatest girl ever and the feelings I have when im around her are indescribable. Everything right now is awesome the only thing that could go wrong will happen on April 18.

It  was a pretty good show for five dollars but when we first got there they tried to say it was a 21 and up show, we were like we came all the way from Jacksonville and they said it was ok. Good times ensued, we got doughnuts, ate pizza and saw a show and ended back in Jacksonville by 2:00 am......but yeah I had my piano and Aural Skills exam today and i made an A on both of them so im quite happy... yeah i made a 37/40 on my aural skills test.since ive made two A's on the past two tests it might bring my "C" up to a "B". I wish i could do that well in music theory. Im hating music theory right now, we are doing chord inversions and it doesnt make a goddamn bit of sense. Other than that the past few days have been cool. I got to march in the Georgia Dome where the falcons play this weekend so that was cool. We got to stay overnight in ATL so i got rather drunk that night. when we were drunk we broke went all the way to the roof of the hotel which was 25 stories high, we had to break the door in but the door had already been tampered with so it was real easy to get in, good times ensued.but yeah there is only one more exhitbition that we have and thats this weekend and then we only have to march for the games...which sorta sucks because we have a good football team this year and they are going to the playoffs, oh well its been a good season i just cant wait until its over so i can finally have some free time i havent been home in forever but me and andrew are finally going to go home this weekend after our exhibition to goto some guys halloween party so that will be cool but yeah thats all i got to say so...later

yeah i havent made a entry in a while, nor sober for that matter....college is great right now for the most part it gets quite stressful though...my music classes seem to be the hardest right now. Music theory is a kick to the balls just because it takes me so long to learn the intervals and the transpostion thing but ill get it eventually, and Aural skills pisses me of because im not to good at learning to sightsing and read rythyms, and as most of you know im white and i have some trouble with rhythyms....but i guess all this music stuff will be worth it in the end because it seems like music is the only thing that keeps me going at times. Being in the southerners right now is getting quite tiring because we always have exhibitions all over georgia and i never have enough time to study for anything....speaking of studying i think im going to lock myself in the music building until they close it at 11, i need to alot of practicing and studying because if not i will end up in the lobby of the dorms until the early hours of the morning.

yeah ive been away for a week for just band camp....band camp at JSU is 2 weeks before school starts and everybody is real serious at jsu about the marching southerners...so the schedule is starts at the parking lot for marching practice at the coliseum at 930-12 and then we have an hour and a half lunch break...we come back for sectionals at 1:30 we play inside til 4 o clock have a two hour dinner break, we come back at six at the colisem parking lot for marching practice from 6-10 o clock at night....needless to say we had the Opening song memorized and the marching in one day...and the music in the opener is the hardest music ive ever ever had to march to and we marching at around 190 beats a minute with 24 sets in the opener. in the opener alone we have the best songs JSU has every played including Festive Overture, Symphony 10, Bottle Dance from the play Fiddler on the Roof, Malaguena, and Stravinsksy's Firebird Suite. The people there are so awesome too they care so much about the band and is almost ridiculous how awesome we have become in just the first week, but everyone says we still need to step up ad get alot better....if we were ever that good in a week at hewitt the apocalypse we be happening because people at HT never cared enough....but oh yeah i play a 20-J (tuba) which weighs around 52 pounds and the give us a shitty strap for carrying it so my collar bone feels like it is going to break everyday and I have a bruise on my side from carrying it....and since Im a rookie 20-j (tuba) player that means im a toad and they give me a nickname with a little initation, well my nickname is Hanson, as in those fags that sang MMMbop.....oh well it couldve been worse,Ben Nichols nickname is the Pickle Tickler....but all in all ive had a good time.....There has been partys everynight and ive had the chance to get beer and anything else i want but i choose not too sometimes because i could toally not work in marching pratice while being hungover....but yeah im going back to JSU tonight i just wanted to update and tell everyone what ive been doing while im gone..........

yep im all packed up....ready to go, hopefully i dont party toooo much while im there cuz I dont need to fuck up and drop out....oh well....i think i will be fine.....


goodbye to all,  for now atleast...

yeah this morning i was going down clay trussville road going to the highschool and some clay chalkville fuckboy pulls out in front of me when i had he green light! am i mistaken but isnt he supposed to yield to me? i believe so. Everyone was ok but my right headlight is busted yet it still seems to work. His car is a bit worse than mine the metal on his car is pinching his back right tire and it wouldnt move. Oh well he deserves it for pulling out in front of me. I tried to dodge him but if i kept going any further to the left i wouldve had a head on collision with someone else...And some girl in his car even said "you sped up when you saw us!!" and i was like "why would i speed up? to make even more damage?" what a dumb little 9th grader she has no clue how to drive much less did she have the right to tell me what i did wrong especially since i didnt even do so....Oh well fuck it their insurance will pay for it....

orlando was cool...though i got sick a few times i managed to have a good time...the hulk was the best rollercoaster ever, spiderman 3d ride was pretty good, dueling dragons was good....universal studios was pretty lame, islands of adventure kicked it in the balls. sypmhonic band performed well though we didnt win the overall contest but we won the parade and we won our class (though we had no competition)...there was a dance/social they had for all the band fags and me and jess cleared it out which was pretty easy....though it was hard to make a pit to rap music we still manges to do so...then some black guy came over and made it a dance contest and i felt like i was in the movie "you got served" so i backed on up out of that...then some security guard  douchebag told me and jess " that we had to stop the violent shit,"...the trip was good but i missed melissa and the only other thing i had to complain about is that they didnt give us much time to sleep but the parks were pretty good so i couldnt complain.....all in all it wasnt that bad for my last spring trip with the band ....

being catholic is so weird especially when you dont even believe what they say to you.i personally dont believe in catholicism but i guess you could say im catholic by heritage? me being very italian i guess i had no way of getting out of it so i had to goto church tonight because it being holy week.this stuff is so weird considering it doesnt make any sense to me.i mean i want to believe in some sort of higher being or god and what not but i just havent had it explained to me in a way that could logically understand it and catholcism or any form of christianity or any religion just doesnt make any sense to me at all.oh well maybe one day i can believe in something but for now i guess i will be confused.but enough about religion....

man i hate drama and or theater. i dont know why but it just seems like the shittiest art form there is mainly because i dont see what is soo "artsy" about acting like you are someone else. maybe i hate it just because of the drama program at my school sucks because it just all the sudden became the "cool" thing to do and it makes me sick. maybe its just the play itself or possibly just the same people im tired of seeing on stage acting a fool....maybe one day i can appreciate it for a good art form but while im at hewitt i think i will just see it as a way to get out of class for a few hours.....i have plenty of friends hopefully they dont get offended because its not them, they just need to tell the people that always get the lead role to give it a break they arent as good as they think they are nor are they as funny...

So i go up to Jacksonville State (where im going next year) to hear their Chamber Winds and their Wind Ensemble. In the middle of the concert the director says he is going to recognize 2 highschool students in the audience that are being awarded FULL scholarship. So I start wondering who it could be and i was thinking it could be me considering i tried out for it. BUT no they say the last name i wanted to hear: Ben Nichols.....I felt like total shit for the rest of the concert because i thought i did good enough on my tryout to get a full scholarship but when i heard his name i wanted to throw up. So the concert ends I grab my balls and congratulate Ben and when im about to leave I see the director and he looks at me in shock and he said " Oh my God if I wouldve known you were here i would mentioned your name too....You got a full scholarship".......it was one of greatest moments ever.....im so happy
